Now, those of us who have served in four language congregations will also remember

00:14:04.429 --> 00:14:11.429
when a new publication in English might not be available in another language for several years.

00:14:11.429 --> 00:14:15.429
Study articles, trailed by several months.

00:14:15.429 --> 00:14:20.429
That's before it became possible for the branches to do simultaneous printing.

00:14:20.429 --> 00:14:22.429
Here's how it worked.

00:14:22.429 --> 00:14:25.429
Material in English would be mailed to the branches,

00:14:25.429 --> 00:14:28.429
regular mail, for translation.

00:14:28.429 --> 00:14:32.429
And if the translators had a question about the meaning of a sentence in English,

00:14:32.429 --> 00:14:36.429
they would use regular mail to send their question to headquarters.

00:14:36.429 --> 00:14:40.429
In time, headquarters would answer back by regular mail.

00:14:40.429 --> 00:14:43.429
And this back and forth, it could take quite a while,

00:14:43.429 --> 00:14:47.429
and in some countries, mail service was poor.

00:14:47.429 --> 00:14:52.429
Now, today, thanks to special computer programs or brothers have developed

00:14:52.429 --> 00:14:56.429
and the ability to communicate electronically and some other factors,

00:14:56.429 --> 00:15:01.429
we're able to release most language editions simultaneously with the English.

00:15:01.429 --> 00:15:05.429
What, an improvement?

00:15:05.429 --> 00:15:07.429
Now, speaking of our literature,

00:15:07.429 --> 00:15:14.429
do you realize that it's been some 31 years since the decision was made that in the United States,

00:15:14.429 --> 00:15:18.429
we'd no longer ask for a contribution for our literature?

00:15:18.429 --> 00:15:21.429
Later, the arrangement was extended worldwide.

00:15:21.429 --> 00:15:26.429
That's been a real blessing for our brothers.

